data.chText: 令人尴尬的；使人难堪的
不要问不好回答的问题。

data.enText: You've put me in an awkward position.
an awkward customer (= a person who is difficult to deal with)

data.chText: 关于让他来这事请你不要作梗。
data.enText: Please don't be awkward about letting him come.
Have I come at an awkward time?

data.chText: （因形状、设计而）产生困难的，危险的
data.enText: difficult or dangerous because of its shape or design

data.chText: 这只箱子一个人很不好搬。
data.enText: This box is very awkward for one person to carry.
not moving in an easy way; not comfortable

data.chText: 他试着跳舞，但是太笨拙，太别扭。
data.enText: He tried to dance, but he was too clumsy and awkward.

data.chText: 我肯定睡的姿势不舒适——我全身疼痛。
data.enText: I must have slept in an awkward position─I'm aching all over.

data.chText: 她笨重地摔了一跤，摔断了踝关节。
data.enText: She fell awkwardly and broke her ankle.

data.chText: 她用笑声掩饰她的难堪。
data.enText: She laughed to cover up her feeling of awkwardness.

ex.chText: 大笨熊摇头时非常可笑。
ex.enText: The clumsy bear is very funny when shaking its head.

ex.chText: 她笨嘴笨舌地安慰我们。
ex.enText: She made a clumsy attempt to comfort us.

ex.chText: 穿着这双笨重的鞋走路真费劲。
ex.enText: It's not easy walking in these clumsy shoes.

synonyms.bx: 指人、动物、动作或语言笨拙的；也指物体笨重、难以使用的。

ex.chText: 他虽然已经长大成人，但依然用不好筷子。
ex.enText: Adult as he is, he is still awkward with chopsticks.
This heavy ax is awkward to use.

synonyms.bx: 指动作不优雅、不舒服的；也指物体因形状等使用不便的。

ex.enText: The blundering guy went the wrong way.

synonyms.bx: 指因粗心和愚笨而常出错的，通常作定语。

ex.enText: That guy is a bungling oaf.

ex.chText: 我从未见过这样蹩脚的演出。
ex.enText: I've never seen such a bungling performance.

synonyms.bx: 指因犯愚蠢的错误而把事情搞糟的，通常作定语。

example: ill at ease among eddies of people he didn't know
they arrived at an awkward time
awkward (or embarrassing or difficult) moments in the discussion
an awkward pause followed his remark
in the unenviable position of resorting to an act he had planned to save for the climax of the campaign

tr: not elegant or graceful in expression
example: if the rumor is true, can anything be more inept than to repeat it now?

tr: lacking grace or skill in manner or movement or performance
example: too awkward with a needle to make her own clothes
his clumsy fingers produced an awkward knot

tr: difficult to handle or manage especially because of shape
example: the cello, a rather ungainly instrument for a girl

value.def: An awkward situation is embarrassing and difficult to deal with.

example.ex: I was the first to ask him awkward questions but there'll be harder ones to come...
example.tran: 我是第一个向他提出尴尬问题的人，不过还会有人问更难回答的问题。

example.ex: There was an awkward moment as couples decided whether to stand next to their partners.
example.tran: 大家在决定是否要站到自己配偶身旁时，这一刻令人尴尬。

value.tran: 使人尴尬的；难处理的；棘手的

example.ex: There was an awkwardly long silence.
example.tran: 有很长一段时间陷入了难堪的沉默。

value.def: Something that is awkward to use or carry is difficult to use or carry because of its design. A job that is awkward is difficult to do.

example.ex: It was small but heavy enough to make it awkward to carry...
example.tran: 它虽然小，但很重，不便携带。

example.ex: Full-size tripods can be awkward, especially if you're shooting a low-level subject.
example.tran: 标准尺寸的三脚架可能会不便于使用，用于拍摄低角度的物体时尤其如此。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ to-inf

value.tran: 难使用的；难携带的；（工作）难处理的

example.ex: The autoexposure button is awkwardly placed under the lens release button.
example.tran: 自动曝光按钮安装在镜头脱卸按钮下面，十分不便。

value.def: An awkward movement or position is uncomfortable or clumsy.

example.ex: Amy made an awkward gesture with her hands.
example.tran: 埃米笨拙地做了个手势。

example.ex: He fell awkwardly and went down in agony clutching his right knee...
example.tran: 他笨拙地摔倒了，痛苦地抱住右膝倒在地上。

example.ex: He lay beside her awkwardly, propped on an elbow.
example.tran: 他用一只胳膊肘支着身体，别扭地躺在她旁边。

value.def: Someone who feels awkward behaves in a shy or embarrassed way.

example.ex: Women frequently say that they feel awkward taking the initiative in sex...
example.tran: 女人们经常说她们不好意思在性生活上采取主动。

example.ex: He was rather awkward with his godson.
example.tran: 在教子面前，他非常局促不安。

value.tran: 害羞的；尴尬的；局促不安的

example.ex: 'This is Malcolm,' the girl said awkwardly, to fill the silence.
example.tran: 女孩尴尬地说了句“这是马尔科姆”，打破了沉默。

example.ex: He displayed all the awkwardness of adolescence.
example.tran: 他表现出了青春期的各种羞涩不安。

value.def: If you say that someone is awkward, you are critical of them because you find them unreasonable and difficult to live with or deal with.

example.ex: She's got to an age where she is being awkward.

value.tran: 不可理喻的；难打交道的；难相处的
